Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows markedly elevated creatinine, low total CO₂, and significant proteinuria, indicating acute or chronic renal dysfunction with possible metabolic acidosis. Urine findings (cloudy, brown, low specific gravity, high protein, glucose, and ketones) suggest impaired renal concentrating ability and possible nephrotic syndrome or diabetic nephropathy, though HbA1c is low. No evidence of urinary infection. Prompt nephrology evaluation is recommended.
